\maketitle
\begin{abstract}
We report on results of systematic numerical studies of two-dimensional
electron gas systems
subject to a perpendicular magnetic field, with a high Landau
level partially filled by electrons. Our results are strongly suggestive of
a breakdown of translational symmetry and the 
presence of crystalline order in the
ground state. This is in sharp contrast with the physics of the lowest and
first excited Landau levels, and in good qualitative agreement
with earlier Hartree-Fock studies. Experimental implications of our results 
are discussed.
\end{abstract}

